  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">The epigrams attributed to Sappho of Lesbos consist of twelve short poetic passages. In the ancient world, an epigram was originally a verse inscription intended for monuments or votive offerings, conventionally composed in elegiac couplets. However, no surviving ancient source references a distinct collection of Sappho’s work under this specific title. Her extant corpus is fragmentary lyric poetry, organized in modern scholarly editions by fragment number rather than by a separate category of epigrams.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The themes present in these epigrammatic passages align with Sappho’s broader lyric concerns, which include intense personal emotion, often expressing love and desire directed toward women; invocations to deities such as Aphrodite; lamentation for separation and absence; imagery drawn from the natural world, including flora, the sea, and celestial bodies, used to mirror emotional states; and contexts involving ritual and ceremony, such as weddings or religious observances.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">Sappho’s poetry was originally arranged in nine books according to meter but survives only in fragments. These fragments have been transmitted through later quotations by other authors, papyrus discoveries such as the Cologne Papyrus, and medieval parchment copies. No manuscript preserves a discrete work titled <strong>Epigrams</strong>; the twelve passages likely represent a modern editorial grouping of fragments that possess epigrammatic qualities of brevity and pointed expression.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">Sappho, celebrated in antiquity as the “Tenth Muse,” exerted a profound influence on later Greek and Roman literature. The personal voice and concision found in her fragments are considered precursors to the developed Hellenistic epigram tradition. This influence, however, derives from her lyric poetry as a whole, not from an independently attested collection of epigrams.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.1.1",
      "text": "Παῖδες, ἄφωνος ἐοῖσα τότ’ ἐννέπω, αἴ τις ἔρηται,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.1.2",
      "text": "φωνὰν ἀκαμάταν κατθεμένα πρὸ ποδῶν·",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.1.3",
      "text": "„Αἰθοπίᾳ με κόρᾳ Λατοῦς ἀνέθηκεν Ἀρίστα",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.1.4",
      "text": "Ἑρμοκλειδαία τῶ Σαϋναϊάδα,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.5.1",
      "text": "σὰ πρόπολος, δέσποινα γυναικῶν· ᾇ σὺ χαρεῖσα",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 269.5.2",
      "text": "πρόφρων ἁμετέραν εὐκλέισον γενεάν.“",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 489.1.1",
      "text": "Τιμάδος ἅδε κόνις, τὰν δὴ πρὸ γάμοιο θανοῦσαν",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 489.1.2",
      "text": "δέξατο Φερσεφόνας κυάνεος θάλαμος,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 489.1.3",
      "text": "ἇς καὶ ἀποφθιμένας πᾶσαι νεοθᾶγι σιδάρῳ",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 489.1.4",
      "text": "ἅλικες ἱμερτὰν κρατὸς ἔθεντο κόμαν.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 505.1",
      "text": "Τῷ γριπεῖ Πελάγωνι πατὴρ ἐπέθηκε Μενίσκος",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 505",
      "text": "κύρτον καὶ κώπαν, μνᾶμα κακοζοΐας.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    }
  ],
